&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CT Superintendent Radiographer - 12 month maternity cover&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic, passionate and motivated team player to take up the position of CT Superintendent Radiographer, to &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;cover a 12month maternity vacancy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will join the Imaging team and will manage the rotational and cross-sectional Radiographers. The overarching aim of this role is to ensure the efficient and effective delivery of the CT and ED CT service within Chelsea and Westminster Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will work closely with all staff within the department (Radiographers, Nurses, Consultant Radiologists, SpR’s, Admin &amp; Clerical staff and Service lead).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our department is going through a significant period of change and improvement. In particular, our CT department will be replacing both CT scanners this financial year and the procurement process is already well under way. This is an incredibly exciting time for Chelsea &amp; Westminster and there is huge opportunity for the interim Superintendent, to play a pivotal role in managing change within the CT service provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
